00:58:41.960 --> 00:58:50.320
On a simple program, I'm focused really—my whole, like, purpose is to help software developers live better lives in all areas of their life.

00:58:50.380 --> 00:59:00.560
Because I have this holistic view, and I feel like if you become a better person in all the areas of your life, you're going to be better in everything that you do, from your career, making money, to being a better programmer.

00:59:00.560 --> 00:59:02.440
And there's not enough focus on that.

00:59:02.440 --> 00:59:04.380
So a simple programmer—

00:59:04.380 --> 00:59:10.760
Like, for example, if you're in better health, you have better fitness, then you probably have more energy to focus on your job.

00:59:10.760 --> 00:59:13.400
Like, there's a lot of secondary knock-on effect, right?

00:59:13.400 --> 00:59:14.580
Oh, yeah, exactly.

00:59:14.780 --> 00:59:23.120
